browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/notes
server-->browser: HTML-code
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/main.css
server-->browser: main.css
browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/main.js
server-->browser: main.js

spa.js requests JSON from server

browser->server: HTTP GET https://fullstack-exampleapp.herokuapp.com/data.json
server-->browser: [{ content: "HTML is easy", date: "2019-05-23" }, ...]

spa.js stores the elements in the "notes" global variable
spa.js tells the browser to draw the JSON elements as <li>

user writes something on the text box and presses the button labeled "Save"

spa.js prevents the redirect by preventing default behaviour
spa.js stores the value of the textbox and the timestamp
spa.js redraws the list withe the inclusion of the new message
spa.js sends the contents of the message, converted to JSON, to the server with a POST request
